Description: Shoulder sherd of North Ionian black-figured pottery vessel probably krater or dinos; interior: reserved; exterior: white slip; body of bull to right with head lowered, lion paws on bull’s neck and horns; painted black with incised details.
Curator's comments: May belong to same pot as 1888,0601.539b. Thickness and curvature do not encourage a connection with 1888,0601.539c-e. Pencil '981'.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1170)
